From: AgenticBrowser <build@agentic-browser.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Set consistent window position and outer dimensions

Detection vector: window.outerWidth/outerHeight, window.screenX/screenY
reveal the browser window's position relative to the screen. In headless
mode these values are 0 or match the viewport, which is a detection
signal. Real browsers have non-zero values (taskbar offset, title bar).

This patch ensures consistent window geometry that matches a real
browser's default window position.

Surface: system
Closes: PHANTOM_WINDOW_HEIGHT, window geometry fingerprinting

--- a/content/browser/renderer_host/render_widget_host_view_base.cc
+++ b/content/browser/renderer_host/render_widget_host_view_base.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ void RenderWidgetHostViewBase::GetScreenInfo(ScreenInfo* result) {
+  // AgenticBrowser: override screen rect to match the configured
+  // fingerprint profile. Uses --ab-screen=WxH,Dx for dimensions and
+  // scale factor, and --ab-screen-avail=WxH for available work area.
